Sausage and White Bean Soup
  --Cook's Country

1 tbsp evoo
1 lb hot italian sausage, casings removed
1 onion, chopped fine
3 garlic cloves, sliced thin
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes
4 c chicken broth
15 oz can cannellini beans, rinsed
1 1/2 c canned crushed tomatoes
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp pepper
3 oz (3 c) baby spinach

Heat oil in dutch oven over medium heat until shimmering. Add sausage and cook, breaking up meat with wooden spoon, until no longer pink, ~4 min. Add onion, garlic, and pepper flakes and cook until onion is softened, 3-5 min. Stir in broth, beans, tomatoes, salt, and pepper and bring to boil, scraping up any fond. Reduce heat to medium low, cover, and simmer until flavors have melded, ~15 min. Off heat, stir in spinach. Season with sal and pepper to taste. Serve.
